overview: "The user wanted to improve the aesthetics of their sleep
  questionnaire app, which they felt was too generic. The agent conducted a
  comprehensive review of the app's visual design, identifying issues with the
  color palette, backgrounds, form elements, and overall visual interest. The
  approach involved a multi-step implementation: first, a new calming,
  sleep-themed color palette was introduced. Then, the main QuestionnaireForm
  and IntroSection were significantly redesigned with subtle background
  elements, improved progress indicators, and engaging feature cards. Key UI
  components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders were polished, and
  section groupings were transformed into more inviting cards. Finally, the
  ReportSection was updated to align with the new aesthetic, featuring
  consistent card headers and refined content styling. The outcome is a more
  professional, calming, and visually appealing application that better suits
  its purpose as a sleep health assessment tool."
